President Trump delivered remarks at the Motera Stadium in Ahmedabad, India, expressing his gratitude to Prime Minister Modi and emphasizing the strong friendship between the United States and India. He praised India's progress and economic growth, highlighting achievements such as lifting millions of people out of poverty, expanding access to electricity and the internet, and improving infrastructure. President Trump also announced plans to strengthen defense cooperation between the two countries and to sign deals for the sale of military equipment to India. He emphasized the commitment of both nations to fight against terrorism and to deepen economic ties. President Trump concluded his remarks by expressing admiration for India's cultural heritage and the strength and spirit of the Indian people.